DML - SQL statements that are used to work with data in the objects 
(add, modify. voew and delete data)

SELECT - displays data of DB table or view. It is the most commonly used SQL statement and can be used 
          to query data from one or more tables. and simultaneously it can transform and aggegate data that it returns.
INSERT - adds data to a DB table
UPDATE - modifies existing data from a table
DELETE - removes existing data from a table
MERGE - performs a combination of INSERT, UPDATE, and DELETE statements in a single statement
